            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Hd1e108">Rubrica 4</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De ratione morali consideratione</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e114">
               De 
               <lb ed="#O"/>ratione morali considerantione. Rubrica 4
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e115">Plato in menone</ref> ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e123">Quotiens ab<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>sque 
               mente audet homo leditur 
               <lb ed="#O"/>quotiens uero cum mente proficitur.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e135">
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e135">ARistoteles ethicorum libro 1. capitulo 8. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e141">omnia 
               <lb ed="#O"/>consonant rationi.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e147">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e146">Idem magnorum 
               <lb ed="#O"/>moralium libro 3 capitulo 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e149">Que fiunt absque ra<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tione 
               iudicante directiones a fortu<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>na 
               sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e152">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e159">Idem physicorum libro 8. capitulo 3</ref> 
               <lb ed="#O"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e154">Ordinatio omnis ratio est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e160">
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e172">TUllius tusculanarum questionum 
               <lb ed="#O"/>libro. 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e164">Munus animi est ratione bene uti. 
               <lb ed="#O"/>¶ Sapientis animus ita semper affectus 
               <lb ed="#O"/>est ut ratione optime utatur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e174">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e185">libro 4.</ref> 
               <lb ed="#O"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e176">Bene ad hibita ratio cernit quid op<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>timum 
               sit neglecta uero multis im<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>plicatur 
               erroribus. ¶ Nichil sine 
               <lb ed="#O"/>ratione recte fieri potest</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e186">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e199">Idem de legibus
               <lb ed="#O"/>libro 1.</ref> ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e188">Quid est non dicam in homine 
               <lb ed="#O"/>sed in omni caelo atquem terra ratione diui<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>nius 
               que cum adoleuit perfecta est 
               <lb ed="#O"/>nominatur rite sapientia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e198">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e216">libro 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e202">lex 
               <lb ed="#O"/>uera atque princeps apta ad iubendum 
               <pb ed="#O" n="104-r"/>
               <cb ed="#O" n="a"/>
               <lb ed="#O"/>et ad uetandum ratio est recta.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e208">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e227">Idem 
               <lb ed="#O"/>de fine bonorum et malorum libro 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e210">rationis
               <lb ed="#O"/>perfectio est uirtus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e216">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e240">Idem de natura deorum 
               <lb ed="#O"/>libro 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e218">Nichil est mente et ratione melius.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e221">
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e253">SEneca epistolarum ad lucillum libro 5. epistola 
               <lb ed="#O"/>8</ref> ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e225">Siuis omnia tibi subiicere 
               <lb ed="#O"/>subiice te rationi.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e231">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e265">libro 8. epistola 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e235">Ratio nichil 
               <lb ed="#O"/>aliud est quam incorpus humanum 
               <lb ed="#O"/>pars diuini spiritus mersa. ¶ Nullum bo<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>num 
               fine ratione est. ¶ Quicquid ra ratio 
               <lb ed="#O"/>commendat solidum et eternum est firmat
               <lb ed="#O"/>animum attollitque futurum semper in 
               <lb ed="#O"/>excelso. ¶ Uirtus non aliud quam 
               <lb ed="#O"/>recta ratio est ¶ Omnes uirtutes ra<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tiones 
               sunt. ¶ Sequitur ratio naturam quid ergo 
               <lb ed="#O"/>est ratio nature imitatio.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e254">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e288">18 t. epistola 2</ref>
               <lb ed="#O"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e256">Ratione valentius nichil est casum dolorem<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>que 
               et iniuriam subigit. ¶ Ama ra<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tionem 
               huius te amor contra durissima 
               <lb ed="#O"/>armabit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e266">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e301">17 t. epistola 4. et pe.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e268">Omnia ad 
               <lb ed="#O"/>rationem reuocanda sunt</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e274">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e315">Idem de 
               <lb ed="#O"/>beneficiis libro 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e278">Nichil sine ratione faci<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>endum 
               est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e284">
               <!--line bumps down-->
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e327">LEx diges. ti. de <!--line. bumps up--> legibus. l. infrascripta.</ref> <!--line bumps back down--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e288">Non omnium que ad ma<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>ioribus 
               constituta sunt ratio reddi 
               <lb ed="#O"/>potest.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e297">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e339">t. ad le. acquilis. l. ita uulne<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>ratus</ref> 
               ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e299">Multa iure ciuili contra rationem 
               <lb ed="#O"/>disputandi pro utilitate communi recep<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>ta 
               sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e307">
               <!--line bumps down-->
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e354">MAxi<!--line bumps up-->mianus</ref> ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e311">Plus ratio quam ius <!--line bumps back down--> ceca ualere solet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-d1e317">
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Rd1e366">CAssiodorus epistolarum libro 1. epistola 9</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d46602-Qd1e321">Fi<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>dem 
               siquidem rerum a ratione colli<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>gimus 
               que nunquam desiderantibus 
               <lb ed="#O"/>absconditur si suis uestigiis perqui<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>ratur.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
